    <!-- Terms of Service Strings -->
    <string name="label_last_updated_date">Last Updated: October 24, 2023</string>
    <string name="terms_section_1_title">1. Acceptance of Terms</string>
    <string name="terms_section_1_body">By accessing or using the Canteen Management System (the \"Service\"), you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service. If you do not agree to all of the terms and conditions, you may not access or use the Service. These terms constitute a legally binding agreement between you and our administration.</string>
    <string name="terms_section_2_title">2. User Responsibilities</string>
    <string name="terms_section_2_body">As a registered staff member or administrator, you are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your account credentials. You agree to:</string>
    <string name="terms_bullet_1">• Provide accurate and complete information during registration.</string>
    <string name="terms_bullet_2">• Notify the administration immediately of any unauthorized use of your account.</string>
    <string name="terms_bullet_3">• Ensure that your use of the platform complies with internal corporate policies.</string>
    <string name="terms_bullet_4">• Abstain from any activity that interferes with the performance of the canteen operations.</string>
    <string name="terms_section_3_title">3. Service Availability</string>
    <string name="terms_section_3_body">While we strive to maintain 99.9% uptime, we do not guarantee that the Service will be uninterrupted or error-free. Maintenance windows are typically scheduled during off-peak hours (11:00 PM - 3:00 AM) to minimize disruption to meal service schedules.</string>
    <string name="terms_section_4_title">4. Data Management &amp; Privacy</string>
    <string name="terms_section_4_body">Your data is processed in accordance with our Privacy Policy. We collect transaction data, meal preferences, and balance information solely for the purpose of optimizing canteen services and ensuring efficient inventory management. All financial transactions are encrypted using enterprise-grade security protocols.</string>
    <string name="terms_section_5_title">5. Limitation of Liability</string>
    <string name="terms_section_5_body">Under no circumstances shall the administration be liable for any direct, indirect, incidental, or consequential damages resulting from the use or inability to use the Service, including but not limited to dietary discrepancies or transaction delays.</string>
    <string name="terms_section_6_title">6. Amendments</string>
    <string name="terms_section_6_body">We reserve the right to modify these terms at any time. Changes will be effective immediately upon posting to this screen. Your continued use of the Service after changes are posted constitutes your acceptance of the new terms.</string>
